                   "message":  "STATUS-DOC-OPENSAVE-RECONCILE: prepend the editor Open/Save surface (#264-#281) into the state docs\n\nAudit P2 / Finding 2 — the four top-level state docs were last reconciled at\n7472467 (ISSUE-256), before the #264-#281 editor in-app Open/Save arc, so they\nwere stale/silent on the whole surface. plans/BASELINE.md actively asserted the\nSAVE direction had \"no path at all\" and in-app open / \"File -\u003e Open\" was\n\"absent\" — both false post-#264-#281.\n\nForward-only prepend (the ISSUE-256 4-doc pattern). Docs-only, 0 code,\n0 Cargo.toml, 28 insertions(+), 0 deletions.\n\n- plans/BASELINE.md: new \"### 2026-06-01 - Editor Open/Save surface landed\n  (#264-#281)\" subsection above the byte-identical 2026-05-28 entry, marking\n  Gap 1 (scene/project persistence - SAVE direction) and the \"non-CLI open/load\n  UX absent\" item CLOSED, source-grounded (save_scene_world_to_path /\n  save_project_world_to_path / handle_open_request / replace_world / SaveSource).\n- Status.md + HANDOFF.md: parallel \"Snapshot: 2026-06-01\" blockquote prepended\n  above the 2026-05-28 ISSUE-256 snapshot.\n- change.md: a 2026-06-01 entry inserted between the ISSUE-256 entry and the\n  pinned REPO TRANSFER line.\n\nAnti-over-claim: closes ONLY the Open/Save gaps. Save-As to a NEW .rge-project\ntree (carried/deferred) and the non-Open/Save gaps (menu-command execution,\ndrag-drop, io-image, World-only CommandBus Action context) are left exactly as\nthe 2026-05-28 ISSUE-256 entry records. The 2026-05-11-grounded one-page summary\npillars and all prior dated entries are byte-identical (pure prepend).\n\nGate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
